		line and column heghlighting
:set cursorcolumn      serves a lot         to remove :set cursorcolumn!  or :set nocursorline
:set cursorline			serves a lot
		
		BASIC WAYS TO INSERT
go to the end of the line and inser (right)---> A       and left--> I
insert on line down--> o       and up--> O

		delete charater and word
delete right--> x    incrementally--> n x   where n=1,2,3,4...
delete comple word, cursor beginning word--> d w    incrementally--> n d w where n=1,2,3,4...
delete complete word--> d i w
		
		CHANGE CHARACTER AN WORDS
delete word and insert--> c w				incrementally----> n c w      n=1,2,3,---n    pendig video 9 chapert3
delete word in cursor position any and inser--->  c i w   incrementally---> n c i w     where n=1,2,3,4,5.....
delete charater and isert---->  s
replace charater with another---> r caracter to enter       example: r a    hola ---->result hala   
delete and insert words in parenthesis()--> c i (   example: (hola como estas)-----result  ()		|
delete and insert words in keys {}--> c i {		example: {hola como esstas}---> result {}			|
delete and insert words in brackets []--> c i [    example: [hola como estas]----> result []		|the cursor must be inside
delete and insert words in quate '' ---> c i '    example: 'hola como estas'----> result ''			|
delete and insert words in quate "" ---> c i " 														|
delete more parenthesis ()----> d a (   example: (hola como estas) ----->result:    nothing		|
						{}----> d a {															|	
						[]----> d a [															|reuslt nothing
						''----> d a '															|
						""----> d a "															|

		DELETE AND CHANGE LINE
delete a line--> d d  and incrementally---> n d d     where n=1,2,3,...
delete and inserte line--> c c incrementally---> n c c where n=1,2,3....

		CUT, COPY, PASTE
mark text--> v						copy=y paste=p
mark text line complete--> V
mark text and copy--> v mark the text and copy  y
mark text and copy and paste--->v  mark y  and paste p
copy line complete--> y y   incrementally--> n y y   where n=1,2,3,...
copy word---> y w    incrementally---> n y w      where n=1,2,3,....
delete line y same copy line----> d d  and for  paste line delete is--->p


